44 char transfer(char* text)
45 {
46  static char savedText[100000];
47  static int counter = 0;
48  static length = 0;
49  if (text != NULL)
50  {
51  strcpy(savedText, text);
52  counter = 0;
53  char* p = text;
54  for (; *p != '\0'; ++p)
55  {
56  // if '\0' happens to be valid data for your app,
57  // then you can (maybe) use some other value as
58  // sentinel
59  }
60  int arraySize = p - text;
61 
62  // now we know the array size, so we can do some thing
63  length = arraySize;
64  return 0;
65  }
66  if (counter < length)
67  {
68  char ret = savedText[counter++];
69  return ret;
70  }
71  else
72  return EOF;
73 }

262 /* Return all but the first "n" matched characters back to the input stream. */
263 #define yyless(n) \
264  do \
265  { \
266  /* Undo effects of setting up yytext. */ \
267  int yyless_macro_arg = (n); \
268  YY_LESS_LINENO(yyless_macro_arg);\
269  *yy_cp = (yy_hold_char); \
270  YY_RESTORE_YY_MORE_OFFSET \
271  (yy_c_buf_p) = yy_cp = yy_bp + yyless_macro_arg - YY_MORE_ADJ; \
272  YY_DO_BEFORE_ACTION; /* set up yytext again */ \
273  } \
274  while ( 0 )

283 #ifndef YY_STRUCT_YY_BUFFER_STATE
284 #define YY_STRUCT_YY_BUFFER_STATE
285 struct yy_buffer_state
286  {
287  FILE *yy_input_file;
288 
289  char *yy_ch_buf; /* input buffer */
290  char *yy_buf_pos; /* current position in input buffer */
291 
292  /* Size of input buffer in bytes, not including room for EOB
293  * characters.
294  */
295  yy_size_t yy_buf_size;
296 
297  /* Number of characters read into yy_ch_buf, not including EOB
298  * characters.
299  */
300  int yy_n_chars;
301 
302  /* Whether we "own" the buffer - i.e., we know we created it,
303  * and can realloc() it to grow it, and should free() it to
304  * delete it.
305  */
306  int yy_is_our_buffer;
307 
308  /* Whether this is an "interactive" input source; if so, and
309  * if we're using stdio for input, then we want to use getc()
310  * instead of fread(), to make sure we stop fetching input after
311  * each newline.
312  */
313  int yy_is_interactive;
314 
315  /* Whether we're considered to be at the beginning of a line.
316  * If so, '^' rules will be active on the next match, otherwise
317  * not.
318  */
319  int yy_at_bol;
320 
321  int yy_bs_lineno;
322  int yy_bs_column;
324  /* Whether to try to fill the input buffer when we reach the
325  * end of it.
326  */
327  int yy_fill_buffer;
328 
329  int yy_buffer_status;
330 
331 #define YY_BUFFER_NEW 0
332 #define YY_BUFFER_NORMAL 1
333  /* When an EOF's been seen but there's still some text to process
334  * then we mark the buffer as YY_EOF_PENDING, to indicate that we
335  * shouldn't try reading from the input source any more. We might
336  * still have a bunch of tokens to match, though, because of
337  * possible backing-up.
338  *
339  * When we actually see the EOF, we change the status to "new"
340  * (via yyrestart()), so that the user can continue scanning by
341  * just pointing yyin at a new input file.
342  */
343 #define YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING 2
344 
345  };
346 #endif /* !YY_STRUCT_YY_BUFFER_STATE */
347 
348 /* Stack of input buffers. */
349 static size_t yy_buffer_stack_top = 0;
350 static size_t yy_buffer_stack_max = 0;
351 static YY_BUFFER_STATE * yy_buffer_stack = 0;
353 /* We provide macros for accessing buffer states in case in the
354  * future we want to put the buffer states in a more general
355  * "scanner state".
356  *
357  * Returns the top of the stack, or NULL.
358  */
359 #define YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ( (yy_buffer_stack) \
360  ? (yy_buffer_stack)[(yy_buffer_stack_top)] \
361  : NULL)
362 
363 /* Same as previous macro, but useful when we know that the buffer stack is not
364  * NULL or when we need an lvalue. For internal use only.
365  */
366 #define YY_CURRENT_BUFFER_LVALUE yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]

412  yy_create_buffer(yyin,YY_BUF_SIZE ); \

457  yyleng = (size_t) (yy_cp - yy_bp); \

14394 This file needs to be turned into a C program using flex

14399  /*#define TTH_GOLD "gold" no longer a distinction*/ /*sf*/

14401 char tth_DOC[]="\n\
14402  Version XXXX (c)1997-2011 Ian Hutchinson\n\
14403  TtH (TeX-to-HTML) translates TeX into HTML.\n\n\
14404 The program is a filter by default: it reads from stdin and writes to stdout.\n\
14405 But a non-switch argument specifies the file[.tex] to translate to file.html.\n\
14406 Diagnostics concerning unknown or untranslated constructs are sent to stderr.\n\n\
14407  Obtain USAGE & switch information by: tth -?\n\
14408  Obtain QUALIFICATIONS by: tth -?q\n\n\
14409 TtH may be used and distributed under the terms of the GPL version 2.\n";
14410 char tth_DOCQ[]="\n\
14411 TeX including mathematics; Plain TeX; LaTeX (2e). \n\
14412 Limitations and special usages:\n\
14413  \\input searches TTHINPUTS not TEXINPUTS. Counter operations are global.\n\
14414  \\catcode changes, tabbing environment, \\usepackage: not supported.\n\
14415  \\epsfbox{file.eps} links or inlines the figure file, depending on -e switch.\n\
14416  \\special{html:stuff} inserts HTML stuff. \\iftth is always true.\n\
14417  \\href{URL}{anchor text} inserts a hypertext anchor pointing to URL.\n\
14418  %%tth: ... passes the rest of the comment to TtH (not TeX) for parsing\n\
14419 \n\

15091  /* Copy whatever the last rule matched to the standard output. */
15092 #ifndef ECHO
15093  /* This used to be an fputs(), but since the string might contain NUL's,
15094  * we now use fwrite().
15095  */
15096 #define ECHO do { if (fwrite( yytext, yyleng, 1, yyout )) {} } while (0)
15097 #endif
15098 
15099  /* Gets input and stuffs it into "buf". number of characters read, or YY_NULL,
15100  * is returned in "result".
15101  */
15102 #define YY_INPUT
15103 #ifndef YY_INPUT
15104 #define YY_INPUT(buf,result,max_size) \
15105  if ( yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_is_interactive ) \
15106  { \
15107  int c = '*'; \
15108  size_t n; \
15109  for ( n = 0; n < max_size && \
15110  (c = transfer(0) /*getc( yyin )*/) != EOF && c != '\n'; ++n ) \
15111  buf[n] = (char) c; \
15112  if ( c == '\n' ) \
15113  buf[n++] = (char) c; \
15114  if ( c == EOF && ferror( yyin ) ) \
15115  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "input in flex scanner failed" ); \
15116  result = n; \
15117  } \
15118  else \
15119  { \
15120  errno=0; \
15121  while ( (result = fread(buf, 1, max_size, yyin))==0 && ferror(yyin)) \
15122  { \
15123  if( errno != EINTR) \
15124  { \
15125  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "input in flex scanner failed" ); \
15126  break; \
15127  } \
15128  errno=0; \
15129  clearerr(yyin); \
15130  } \
15131  }\
15132 \
15133 
15134 #endif
15135 
15136 /* No semi-colon after return; correct usage is to write "yyterminate();" -
15137  * we don't want an extra ';' after the "return" because that will cause
15138  * some compilers to complain about unreachable statements.
15139  */
15140 #ifndef yyterminate
15141 #define yyterminate() return YY_NULL
15142 #endif

15625 /* Define the storable stacked integers */
15626 #define INTDEPTHMAX 30 /* Stack depth*/
15627 #define INTMAX 10 /* Maximum integers */
15628 #define INTERROR 99999 /* Value indicating overflow */
15629 int PUSHEDINTS[INTMAX][INTDEPTHMAX]={{0}};
15630 int PUSHEDINTDEPTHS[INTMAX]={0};
15631 #define TTH_INT_SETPUSH(name,value) \
15632  if(PUSHEDINTDEPTHS[name]<INTDEPTHMAX) {\
15633  PUSHEDINTS[name][++PUSHEDINTDEPTHS[name] ]=value;\
15634  }else{fprintf(stderr,"INT overflow, %s\n","name");++PUSHEDINTDEPTHS[name];}
15635 #define TTH_INT_VALUE(name) \
15636  (PUSHEDINTDEPTHS[name]<=INTDEPTHMAX) ? \
15637  PUSHEDINTS[name][PUSHEDINTDEPTHS[name] ] :\
15638  INTERROR
15639 #define TTH_INT_POP(name) \
15640  if(PUSHEDINTDEPTHS[name]>0){\
15641  PUSHEDINTS[name][PUSHEDINTDEPTHS[name]--]=0;\
15642  }else{fprintf(stderr,"INT underflow, %s\n","name");}

27193 /* yy_get_next_buffer - try to read in a new buffer
27194  *
27195  * Returns a code representing an action:
27196  * EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH -
27197  * EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN - continue scanning from current position
27198  * EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE - end of file
27199  */
27200 static int yy_get_next_buffer (void)
27201 {
27202  register char *dest = yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_ch_buf;
27203  register char *source = (yytext_ptr);
27204  register int number_to_move, i;
27205  int ret_val;
27206 
27207  if ( (yy_c_buf_p) > &yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars) + 1] )
27208  YY_FATAL_ERROR(
27209  "fatal flex scanner internal error--end of buffer missed" );
27210

27212  { /* Don't try to fill the buffer, so this is an EOF. */
27213  if ( (yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr) - YY_MORE_ADJ == 1 )
27214  {
27215  /* We matched a single character, the EOB, so
27216  * treat this as a final EOF.
27217  */
27218  return EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE;
27219  }
27220 
27221  else
27222  {
27223  /* We matched some text prior to the EOB, first
27224  * process it.
27225  */
27226  return EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH;
27227  }
27228  }
27229 
27230  /* Try to read more data. */
27231 
27232  /* First move last chars to start of buffer. */
27233  number_to_move = (int) ((yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr)) - 1;
27234 
27235  for ( i = 0; i < number_to_move; ++i )
27236  *(dest++) = *(source++);
27237 
27238  if ( yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_buffer_status == YY_BUFFER_EOF_PENDING )
27239  /* don't do the read, it's not guaranteed to return an EOF,
27240  * just force an EOF

27242  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars) = 0;
27243 
27244  else
27245  {

27247  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_buf_size - number_to_move - 1;
27248 
27249  while ( num_to_read <= 0 )
27250  { /* Not enough room in the buffer - grow it. */
27251

27253  YY_BUFFER_STATE b = YY_CURRENT_BUFFER;
27254

27261 
27262  if ( new_size <= 0 )

27264  else

27268  /* Include room in for 2 EOB chars. */
27269  yyrealloc((void *) b->yy_ch_buf,b->yy_buf_size + 2 );

27273  b->yy_ch_buf = 0;
27274 
27275  if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )

27289  /* Read in more data. */
27290  //(buf, result, max_size)
27291  if (yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_is_interactive) \
27292  { \
27293  int c = '*'; \
27294  size_t n; \

27359 
27360  (yytext_ptr) = &yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_ch_buf[0];

27365 /* yy_get_previous_state - get the state just before the EOB char was reached */
27366 
27367  static yy_state_type yy_get_previous_state (void)
27368 {
27369  register yy_state_type yy_current_state;
27370  register char *yy_cp;
27371 
27372  yy_current_state = (yy_start);
27373 
27374  for ( yy_cp = (yytext_ptr) + YY_MORE_ADJ; yy_cp < (yy_c_buf_p); ++yy_cp )
27375  {
27376  register YY_CHAR yy_c = (*yy_cp ? yy_ec[YY_SC_TO_UI(*yy_cp)] : 1);
27377  if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
27378  {
27379  (yy_last_accepting_state) = yy_current_state;
27380  (yy_last_accepting_cpos) = yy_cp;
27381  }
27382  while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
27383  {
27384  yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
27385  if ( yy_current_state >= 11276 )
27386  yy_c = yy_meta[(unsigned int) yy_c];
27387  }
27388  yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + (unsigned int) yy_c];
27389  }
27390

27394 /* yy_try_NUL_trans - try to make a transition on the NUL character
27395  *
27396  * synopsis
27397  * next_state = yy_try_NUL_trans( current_state );
27398  */
27399  static yy_state_type yy_try_NUL_trans (yy_state_type yy_current_state )
27400 {
27401  register int yy_is_jam;
27402  register char *yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
27403 
27404  register YY_CHAR yy_c = 1;
27405  if ( yy_accept[yy_current_state] )
27406  {
27407  (yy_last_accepting_state) = yy_current_state;
27408  (yy_last_accepting_cpos) = yy_cp;
27409  }
27410  while ( yy_chk[yy_base[yy_current_state] + yy_c] != yy_current_state )
27411  {
27412  yy_current_state = (int) yy_def[yy_current_state];
27413  if ( yy_current_state >= 11276 )
27414  yy_c = yy_meta[(unsigned int) yy_c];
27415  }
27416  yy_current_state = yy_nxt[yy_base[yy_current_state] + (unsigned int) yy_c];
27417  yy_is_jam = (yy_current_state == 11275);
27418 
27419  return yy_is_jam ? 0 : yy_current_state;
27420 }

27422  static void yyunput (int c, register char * yy_bp )
27423 {
27424  register char *yy_cp;
27425 
27426  yy_cp = (yy_c_buf_p);
27427 
27428  /* undo effects of setting up yytext */
27429  *yy_cp = (yy_hold_char);
27430 
27431  if ( yy_cp < yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_ch_buf + 2 )
27432  { /* need to shift things up to make room */
27433  /* +2 for EOB chars. */
27434  register int number_to_move = (yy_n_chars) + 2;
27435  register char *dest = &yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_ch_buf[
27436  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_buf_size + 2];
27437  register char *source =
27438  &yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_ch_buf[number_to_move];
27439 
27440  while ( source > yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_ch_buf )
27441  *--dest = *--source;
27442 
27443  yy_cp += (int) (dest - source);
27444  yy_bp += (int) (dest - source);
27445  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_n_chars =
27446  (yy_n_chars) = yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_buf_size;
27447 
27448  if ( yy_cp < yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_ch_buf + 2 )
27449  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "flex scanner push-back overflow" );
27450  }
27451 
27452  *--yy_cp = (char) c;
27453 
27454  (yytext_ptr) = yy_bp;
27455  (yy_hold_char) = *yy_cp;
27456  (yy_c_buf_p) = yy_cp;
27457 }

27459 #ifndef YY_NO_INPUT
27460 #ifdef __cplusplus
27461  static int yyinput (void)
27462 #else
27463  static int input (void)
27464 #endif
27465 
27466 {
27467  int c;
27468 
27469  *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
27470 
27471  if ( *(yy_c_buf_p) == YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
27472  {
27473  /* yy_c_buf_p now points to the character we want to return.
27474  * If this occurs *before* the EOB characters, then it's a
27475  * valid NUL; if not, then we've hit the end of the buffer.
27476  */
27477  if ( (yy_c_buf_p) < &yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_ch_buf[(yy_n_chars)] )
27478  /* This was really a NUL. */
27479  *(yy_c_buf_p) = '\0';
27480 
27481  else
27482  { /* need more input */
27483  int offset = (yy_c_buf_p) - (yytext_ptr);
27484  ++(yy_c_buf_p);
27485 
27486  switch ( yy_get_next_buffer( ) )
27487  {
27488  case EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH:
27489  /* This happens because yy_g_n_b()
27490  * sees that we've accumulated a
27491  * token and flags that we need to
27492  * try matching the token before
27493  * proceeding. But for input(),
27494  * there's no matching to consider.
27495  * So convert the EOB_ACT_LAST_MATCH
27496  * to EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE.
27497  */
27498 
27499  /* Reset buffer status. */
27500  yyrestart(yyin );
27501 
27502  /*FALLTHROUGH*/
27503 
27504  case EOB_ACT_END_OF_FILE:
27505  {
27506  if ( yywrap( ) )
27507  return EOF;
27508 
27509  if ( ! (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) )
27510  YY_NEW_FILE;
27511 #ifdef __cplusplus
27512  return yyinput();
27513 #else
27514  return input();
27515 #endif
27516  }
27517 
27518  case EOB_ACT_CONTINUE_SCAN:
27519  (yy_c_buf_p) = (yytext_ptr) + offset;
27520  break;
27521  }
27522  }
27523  }
27524 
27525  c = *(unsigned char *) (yy_c_buf_p); /* cast for 8-bit char's */
27526  *(yy_c_buf_p) = '\0'; /* preserve yytext */
27527  (yy_hold_char) = *++(yy_c_buf_p);
27528 
27529  return c;
27530 }
27531 #endif /* ifndef YY_NO_INPUT */

27538  void yyrestart (FILE * input_file )

27542  yyensure_buffer_stack ();

27555  void yy_switch_to_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
27556 {
27557 
27558  /* TODO. We should be able to replace this entire function body
27559  * with
27560  * yypop_buffer_state();
27561  * yypush_buffer_state(new_buffer);
27562  */
27563  yyensure_buffer_stack ();
27564  if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER == new_buffer )
27565  return;
27566 
27567  if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
27568  {
27569  /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
27570  *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
27571  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
27572  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
27573  }
27574 
27575  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top] = new_buffer;
27576  yy_load_buffer_state( );
27577 
27578  /* We don't actually know whether we did this switch during
27579  * EOF (yywrap()) processing, but the only time this flag
27580  * is looked at is after yywrap() is called, so it's safe
27581  * to go ahead and always set it.
27582  */
27583  (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
27584 }

27591  (yy_hold_char) = *(yy_c_buf_p);
27592 }

27600  YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_create_buffer (FILE * file, int size )
27601 {
27602  YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
27603 
27604  b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc(sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) );
27605  if ( ! b )
27606  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
27607 
27608  b->yy_buf_size = size;
27609 
27610  /* yy_ch_buf has to be 2 characters longer than the size given because
27611  * we need to put in 2 end-of-buffer characters.
27612  */
27613  b->yy_ch_buf = (char *) yyalloc(b->yy_buf_size + 2 );
27614  if ( ! b->yy_ch_buf )
27615  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_create_buffer()" );
27616 
27617  b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
27618 
27619  yy_init_buffer(b,file );
27620 
27621  return b;
27622 }

27628  void yy_delete_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b )
27629 {
27630 
27631  if ( ! b )
27632  return;
27633 
27634  if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER ) /* Not sure if we should pop here. */
27635  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top] = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) 0;
27636 
27637  if ( b->yy_is_our_buffer )
27638  yyfree((void *) b->yy_ch_buf );
27639 
27640  yyfree((void *) b );
27641 }
27642 
27643 /* Initializes or reinitializes a buffer.
27644  * This function is sometimes called more than once on the same buffer,
27645  * such as during a yyrestart() or at EOF.
27646  */
27647  static void yy_init_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b, FILE * file )
27648 
27649 {
27650  int oerrno = errno;
27651 
27652  yy_flush_buffer(b );
27653 
27654  b->yy_input_file = file;
27655  b->yy_fill_buffer = 1;
27656 
27657  /* If b is the current buffer, then yy_init_buffer was _probably_
27658  * called from yyrestart() or through yy_get_next_buffer.
27659  * In that case, we don't want to reset the lineno or column.
27660  */
27661  if (b != YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
27662  b->yy_bs_lineno = 1;
27663  b->yy_bs_column = 0;
27664  }
27665 
27666  b->yy_is_interactive = 1;
27667 
27668  errno = oerrno;
27669 }
27670 
27675  void yy_flush_buffer (YY_BUFFER_STATE b )
27676 {
27677  if ( ! b )
27678  return;
27679 
27680  b->yy_n_chars = 0;
27681 
27682  /* We always need two end-of-buffer characters. The first causes
27683  * a transition to the end-of-buffer state. The second causes
27684  * a jam in that state.
27685  */
27686  b->yy_ch_buf[0] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
27687  b->yy_ch_buf[1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
27688 
27689  b->yy_buf_pos = &b->yy_ch_buf[0];
27690 
27691  b->yy_at_bol = 1;
27692  b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
27693 
27694  if ( b == YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
27695  yy_load_buffer_state( );
27696 }
27697 
27704 void yypush_buffer_state (YY_BUFFER_STATE new_buffer )
27705 {
27706  if (new_buffer == NULL)
27707  return;
27708 
27709  yyensure_buffer_stack();
27710 
27711  /* This block is copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
27712  if ( YY_CURRENT_BUFFER )
27713  {
27714  /* Flush out information for old buffer. */
27715  *(yy_c_buf_p) = (yy_hold_char);
27716  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_buf_pos = (yy_c_buf_p);
27717  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top]->yy_n_chars = (yy_n_chars);
27718  }
27719 
27720  /* Only push if top exists. Otherwise, replace top. */
27721  if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
27722  (yy_buffer_stack_top)++;
27723  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top] = new_buffer;
27724 
27725  /* copied from yy_switch_to_buffer. */
27726  yy_load_buffer_state( );
27727  (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
27728 }
27729 
27734 void yypop_buffer_state (void)
27735 {
27736  if (!YY_CURRENT_BUFFER)
27737  return;
27738 
27739  yy_delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER );
27740  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top] = NULL;
27741  if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) > 0)
27742  --(yy_buffer_stack_top);
27743 
27744  if (YY_CURRENT_BUFFER) {
27745  yy_load_buffer_state( );
27746  (yy_did_buffer_switch_on_eof) = 1;
27747  }
27748 }
27749 
27750 /* Allocates the stack if it does not exist.
27751  * Guarantees space for at least one push.
27752  */
27753 static void yyensure_buffer_stack (void)
27754 {
27755  int num_to_alloc;
27756 
27757  if (!(yy_buffer_stack)) {
27758 
27759  /* First allocation is just for 2 elements, since we don't know if this
27760  * scanner will even need a stack. We use 2 instead of 1 to avoid an
27761  * immediate realloc on the next call.
27762  */
27763  num_to_alloc = 1;
27764  (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyalloc
27765  (num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
27766  );
27767  if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
27768  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
27769 
27770  memset((yy_buffer_stack), 0, num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
27771 
27772  (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
27773  (yy_buffer_stack_top) = 0;
27774  return;
27775  }
27776 
27777  if ((yy_buffer_stack_top) >= ((yy_buffer_stack_max)) - 1){
27778 
27779  /* Increase the buffer to prepare for a possible push. */
27780  int grow_size = 8 /* arbitrary grow size */;
27781 
27782  num_to_alloc = (yy_buffer_stack_max) + grow_size;
27783  (yy_buffer_stack) = (struct yy_buffer_state**)yyrealloc
27784  ((yy_buffer_stack),
27785  num_to_alloc * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*)
27786  );
27787  if ( ! (yy_buffer_stack) )
27788  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yyensure_buffer_stack()" );
27789 
27790  /* zero only the new slots.*/
27791  memset((yy_buffer_stack) + (yy_buffer_stack_max), 0, grow_size * sizeof(struct yy_buffer_state*));
27792  (yy_buffer_stack_max) = num_to_alloc;
27793  }
27794 }
27795 
27802 YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_buffer (char * base, yy_size_t size )
27803 {
27804  YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
27805 
27806  if ( size < 2 ||
27807  base[size-2] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR ||
27808  base[size-1] != YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR )
27809  /* They forgot to leave room for the EOB's. */
27810  return 0;
27811 
27812  b = (YY_BUFFER_STATE) yyalloc(sizeof( struct yy_buffer_state ) );
27813  if ( ! b )
27814  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_buffer()" );
27815 
27816  b->yy_buf_size = size - 2; /* "- 2" to take care of EOB's */
27817  b->yy_buf_pos = b->yy_ch_buf = base;
27818  b->yy_is_our_buffer = 0;
27819  b->yy_input_file = 0;
27820  b->yy_n_chars = b->yy_buf_size;
27821  b->yy_is_interactive = 0;
27822  b->yy_at_bol = 1;
27823  b->yy_fill_buffer = 0;
27824  b->yy_buffer_status = YY_BUFFER_NEW;
27825 
27826  yy_switch_to_buffer(b );
27827 
27828  return b;
27829 }
27830 
27839 YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_string (yyconst char * yystr )
27840 {
27841 
27842  return yy_scan_bytes(yystr,strlen(yystr) );
27843 }
27844 
27852 YY_BUFFER_STATE yy_scan_bytes (yyconst char * yybytes, int _yybytes_len )
27853 {
27854  YY_BUFFER_STATE b;
27855  char *buf;
27856  yy_size_t n;
27857  int i;
27858 
27859  /* Get memory for full buffer, including space for trailing EOB's. */
27860  n = _yybytes_len + 2;
27861  buf = (char *) yyalloc(n );
27862  if ( ! buf )
27863  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of dynamic memory in yy_scan_bytes()" );
27864 
27865  for ( i = 0; i < _yybytes_len; ++i )
27866  buf[i] = yybytes[i];
27867 
27868  buf[_yybytes_len] = buf[_yybytes_len+1] = YY_END_OF_BUFFER_CHAR;
27869 
27870  b = yy_scan_buffer(buf,n );
27871  if ( ! b )
27872  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "bad buffer in yy_scan_bytes()" );
27873 
27874  /* It's okay to grow etc. this buffer, and we should throw it
27875  * away when we're done.
27876  */
27877  b->yy_is_our_buffer = 1;
27878 
27879  return b;
27880 }
27881 
27882  static void yy_push_state (int new_state )
27883 {
27884  if ( (yy_start_stack_ptr) >= (yy_start_stack_depth) )
27885  {
27886  yy_size_t new_size;
27887 
27888  (yy_start_stack_depth) += YY_START_STACK_INCR;
27889  new_size = (yy_start_stack_depth) * sizeof( int );
27890 
27891  if ( ! (yy_start_stack) )
27892  (yy_start_stack) = (int *) yyalloc(new_size );
27893 
27894  else
27895  (yy_start_stack) = (int *) yyrealloc((void *) (yy_start_stack),new_size );
27896 
27897  if ( ! (yy_start_stack) )
27898  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "out of memory expanding start-condition stack" );
27899  }
27900 
27901  (yy_start_stack)[(yy_start_stack_ptr)++] = YY_START;
27902 
27903  BEGIN(new_state);
27904 }
27905 
27906  static void yy_pop_state (void)
27907 {
27908  if ( --(yy_start_stack_ptr) < 0 )
27909  YY_FATAL_ERROR( "start-condition stack underflow" );
27910 
27911  BEGIN((yy_start_stack)[(yy_start_stack_ptr)]);
27912 }
27913 
27914  static int yy_top_state (void)
27915 {
27916  return (yy_start_stack)[(yy_start_stack_ptr) - 1];
27917 }

27942  yyleng = yyless_macro_arg; \
27943  } \
27944  while ( 0 )

28026 static int yy_init_globals (void)
28027 {
28028  /* Initialization is the same as for the non-reentrant scanner.
28029  * This function is called from yylex_destroy(), so don't allocate here.
28030  */
28031 
28032  (yy_buffer_stack) = 0;
28033  (yy_buffer_stack_top) = 0;
28034  (yy_buffer_stack_max) = 0;
28035  (yy_c_buf_p) = (char *) 0;
28036  (yy_init) = 0;
28037  (yy_start) = 0;
28038 
28039  (yy_start_stack_ptr) = 0;
28040  (yy_start_stack_depth) = 0;
28041  (yy_start_stack) = NULL;
28042 
28043 /* Defined in main.c */
28044 #ifdef YY_STDINIT
28045  yyin = stdin;
28046  yyout = stdout;
28047 #else
28048  yyin = (FILE *) 0;
28049  yyout = (FILE *) 0;
28050 #endif
28051 
28052  /* For future reference: Set errno on error, since we are called by
28053  * yylex_init()
28054  */
28055  return 0;
28056 }
28057 
28058 /* yylex_destroy is for both reentrant and non-reentrant scanners. */
28059 int yylex_destroy (void)
28060 {
28061 
28062  /* Pop the buffer stack, destroying each element. */
28063  while(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER){
28064  yy_delete_buffer(YY_CURRENT_BUFFER );
28065  yy_buffer_stack[yy_buffer_stack_top] = NULL;
28066  yypop_buffer_state();
28067  }
28068 
28069  /* Destroy the stack itself. */
28070  yyfree((yy_buffer_stack) );
28071  (yy_buffer_stack) = NULL;
28072 
28073  /* Destroy the start condition stack. */
28074  yyfree((yy_start_stack) );
28075  (yy_start_stack) = NULL;
28076 
28077  /* Reset the globals. This is important in a non-reentrant scanner so the next time
28078  * yylex() is called, initialization will occur. */
28079  yy_init_globals( );
28080 
28081  return 0;
28082 }

28113 void *yyrealloc (void * ptr, yy_size_t size )
28114 {
28115  /* The cast to (char *) in the following accommodates both
28116  * implementations that use char* generic pointers, and those
28117  * that use void* generic pointers. It works with the latter
28118  * because both ANSI C and C++ allow castless assignment from
28119  * any pointer type to void*, and deal with argument conversions
28120  * as though doing an assignment.
28121  */
28122  return (void *) realloc( (char *) ptr, size );
28123 }

28128 }

28461 //*******************************************************************************************************************************
28462 void tth_push(arg)
28463 char arg[];
28464 {
28465  if(tth_debug&16) fprintf(stderr,"tth_push:%s depth:%d\n",\
28466  arg,tth_push_depth);
28467  if(tth_push_depth == TTH_MAXDEPTH) {
28468  fprintf(stderr,
28469  "**** Error Fatal: Attempt to exceed max nesting:%d\n",
28470  tth_push_depth);
28471  TTH_FATAL(6);
28472  }else{
28473  strcpy(tth_closures[tth_push_depth],arg);
28474  strcpy(tth_font_open[tth_push_depth+1],
28475  tth_font_open[tth_push_depth]);
28476  strcpy(tth_font_close[tth_push_depth+1],
28477  tth_font_close[tth_push_depth]);
28478  tth_push_depth++;
28479  }
28480  arg[0]=0;
28481 }
28482 
28483 void tth_pop(arg)
28484 char arg[];
28485 {
28486  if(tth_push_depth < 1){
28487  fprintf(stderr,"**** Error: Fatal. Apparently too many }s.\nCheck for TeX errors or incompatibilities before line %d,\nnext material ",tth_num_lines);
28488  /*TTH_FATAL(1);*/
28489  yy_push_state(error);
28490  tth_ercnt=40;
28491  }else{
28492  tth_push_depth--;
28493  strcpy(arg,tth_closures[tth_push_depth]);
28494  if(tth_debug&16) fprintf(stderr,"tth_pop:%s depth:%d\n",\
28495  arg,tth_push_depth);
28496  }
28497 }

28499 /* ********************************************************************
28500  Process epsbox. If epsftype=0 put link. Arg is the file name.
28501  epsftype=1 Convert the ps or eps file to a gif reference.
28502  epsftype=2 Ditto but inline it. epsftype=3 inline an iconized version.*/
28503 void tth_epsf(arg,epsftype)
28504 char *arg;
28505 int epsftype;
28506 {
28507 #define NCONV 2
28508 #define NGTYPES 3
28509  char *gtype[NGTYPES]={"png","gif","jpg"};
28510  char commandstr[150]={0};
28511  char filestr[150]={0};
28512  char filestr1[150]={0};
28513  char filestr2[150]={0};
28514  FILE *giffile;
28515  int sys=SUCCESS;
28516  int c,i,psfound;
28517  char *ext;
28518  char eqstr[1]; /*dummy here for tthfunc*/
28519  *eqstr=0; /*silence warnings */
28520  ext=arg; /*silence warnings */
28521 if(epsftype==0){
28522  append2(HTMLOUT,"<a href=\"%s\">Figure</a>",arg);
28523 }else{
28524  c=0;
28525  for(i=1;i<=(strlen(arg)<4 ? strlen(arg) : 4);i++){
28526  ext=arg+strlen(arg)-i;
28527  if(*ext=='.'){
28528  c=i;
28529  break;
28530  }
28531  ext=ext+i;
28532  }
28533  if(c){
28534  if(strcmp(ext,".eps") && strcmp(ext,".EPS")
28535  && strcmp(ext,".ps") && strcmp(ext,".PS")
28536  && strcmp(ext,".pdf") && strcmp(ext,".PDF"))
28537  {
28538  fprintf(stderr,"Not a [e]ps file: %s, no conversion\n",arg);
28539  if(epsftype==1) append2(HTMLOUT,"<a href=\"%s\">Figure</a>",arg);
28540  if(epsftype==2) append3(HTMLOUT,"<img src=\"%s\" alt=\"%s\" />",arg,arg);
28541  return;
28542  }
28543  }
28544  /* c=length of extension.*/
28545  strcpy(filestr,arg);
28546  giffile=fopen(filestr,"r");
28547  psfound=0;
28548  if(giffile == NULL){ /* Try possible file names */
28549  if(tth_debug&32)fprintf(stderr,"Graphic Input File %s not found.\n",filestr);
28550  if(c==0){
28551  strcat(filestr,".eps");
28552  giffile=fopen(filestr,"r");
28553  if(giffile == NULL){
28554  if(tth_debug&32)fprintf(stderr,"Graphic Input File %s not found.\n",filestr);
28555  strcpy(filestr,arg); strcat(filestr,".ps");
28556  giffile=fopen(filestr,"r");
28557  if(giffile == NULL){
28558  if(tth_debug&32)fprintf(stderr,"Graphic Input File %s not found.\n",filestr);
28559  strcpy(filestr,arg); strcat(filestr,".pdf");
28560  giffile=fopen(filestr,"r");
28561  if(giffile == NULL){
28562  if(tth_debug&32)fprintf(stderr,"Graphic Input File %s not found.\n",filestr);
28563  psfound=0;
28564  strcpy(filestr,arg); /*Restore original name*/
28565  }else{
28566  fprintf(stderr,"Found %s. ",filestr);
28567  psfound=1;
28568  c=4;
28569  }
28570  }else{
28571  fprintf(stderr,"Found %s. ",filestr);
28572  psfound=1;
28573  c=3;
28574  }
28575  }else{
28576  fprintf(stderr,"Found %s. ",filestr);
28577  psfound=1;
28578  c=4;
28579  }
28580  }
28581  }else{psfound=1;}
28582  strcat(filestr1,filestr); /* The file we found for input if any.*/
28583  filestr[strlen(filestr)-c]=0;
28584  sys=SUCCESS+1;
28585  for(c=0;c<NGTYPES;c++){ /* Check for already translated files */
28586  sprintf(filestr2,"%s.%s",filestr,gtype[c]);
28587  if(tth_debug&32)fprintf(stderr,"Trying %s\n",filestr2);
28588  if ((giffile=fopen(filestr2,"r")) != NULL){
28589  fprintf(stderr,"Graphic %s exists. No conversion.\n",filestr2);
28590  strcpy(filestr,filestr2);
28591  sys=SUCCESS;
28592  fclose(giffile);
28593  break;
28594  }
28595  }
28596  if(psfound){
28597  if(sys!=SUCCESS){ /* No existing graphic. Translate. */
28598  for(c=0;c<NCONV;c++){
28599  sprintf(filestr2,"%s.%s",filestr,gtype[c]);
28600  sprintf(commandstr,"ps2%s %s %s",gtype[c],filestr1,filestr2);
28601  if(epsftype==3){ /* Icon version of ps2pnm/gif with 3 arguments */
28602  sprintf(commandstr+strlen(commandstr)," %s_icon.%s",filestr,gtype[c]);
28603  }
28604  fprintf(stderr,"Converting file %s ",filestr1);
28605  if(tth_debug&32)fprintf(stderr,"Command: %s",commandstr);
28606  sys=system(commandstr);
28607  if(sys==SUCCESS){
28608  if((giffile=fopen(filestr2,"r"))!=NULL){
28609  fclose(giffile);
28610  sprintf(filestr1,"%s_icon.%s",filestr,gtype[c]);
28611  strcpy(filestr,filestr2);
28612  break;
28613  }else{sys=SUCCESS+1;}
28614  }
28615  }
28616  }
28617  }
28618  if(sys == SUCCESS){
28619  if(epsftype==1) append2(HTMLOUT,"<a href=\"%s\">Figure</a>",filestr);
28620  if(epsftype==2) append3(HTMLOUT,"<img src=\"%s\" alt=\"%s\" />",filestr,filestr);
28621  if(epsftype==3) append(HTMLOUT,"<a href=\"%s\"><img src=\"%s\" alt=\"%s\" /></a>"
28622  ,filestr,filestr1,filestr1);
28623  }else if(psfound){ /* This can only happen if the system call occurs. */
28624  fprintf(stderr,"**** System call:%s failed.\n",commandstr);
28625  fprintf(stderr,
28626  "**** This failure is NOT in TtH; it is in an auxiliary program.\n");
28627  append2(HTMLOUT,"<a href=\"%s\">Figure</a>",arg);
28628  }else {
28629  fprintf(stderr,"**** No suitable source file for %s\n",arg);
28630  }
28631 }
28632 }

28636 static int indexkey(key,keys,nkeys)
28637 char *key;
28638 char *keys[];
28639 int *nkeys;
28640 {
28641  int i, j;
28642  j=-1;
28643  for(i = *nkeys-1; i>=0; i--) {
28644  if(!strcmp(key,keys[i])) {
28645  j=i;
28646  break;
28647  }
28648  }
28649  return j;
28650 }

28652 static void mkkey(key,keys,nkeys)
28653 char *key;
28654 char *keys[];
28655 int *nkeys;
28656 {
28657  size_t size;
28658  size=strlen(key)+1;
28659  keys[*nkeys]=malloc(size);
28660  strcpy(keys[*nkeys],key);
28661  (*nkeys)++;
28662 }
28663 
28664 static void mkdef(key,keys,def,defs,narg,nargs,nkeys)
28665 char *key;
28666 char *keys[];
28667 char *def;
28668 char *defs[];
28669 int *narg;
28670 int nargs[];
28671 int *nkeys;
28672 {
28673  size_t size;
28674  size=strlen(key)+1;
28675  keys[*nkeys]=malloc(size);
28676  strcpy(keys[*nkeys],key);
28677  size=strlen(def)+1;
28678  defs[*nkeys]=malloc(size);
28679  strcpy(defs[*nkeys],def);
28680  nargs[*nkeys]=*narg;
28681  (*nkeys)++;
28682 }
28683 
28684 static void rmkey(keys,nkeys)
28685 char *keys[];
28686 int *nkeys;
28687 {
28688  if((*nkeys) > 0){
28689  (*nkeys)--;
28690  free(keys[*nkeys]);
28691  keys[*nkeys]=0;
28692  } else {
28693  fprintf(stderr,"**** Error: No keys left to remove\n");
28694  }
28695 }
28696 
28697 static void rmdef(keys,defs,nkeys)
28698 char *keys[];
28699 char *defs[];
28700 int *nkeys;
28701 {
28702  if((*nkeys) > 0){
28703  (*nkeys)--;
28704  free(keys[*nkeys]);
28705  keys[*nkeys]=0;
28706  free(defs[*nkeys]);
28707  defs[*nkeys]=0;
28708  } else {
28709  fprintf(stderr,"**** Error: No defs left to remove\n");
28710  }
28711 }
28712 
28713 void tth_undefine(keys,nkeys,udkey,lkeys)
28714 char *keys[];
28715 int *nkeys;
28716 int udkey;
28717 int lkeys[];
28718  /* Undefine all local keys (lkeys(n)=1) from udkey to nkeys-1 */
28719 {
28720  /*static void rmkey();*/
28721  int i,ig;
28722  ig=0;
28723  for(i=(*nkeys)-1;i>=udkey;i--) {
28724  if(lkeys[i]){
28725  if(tth_debug&4)fprintf(stderr,
28726  "Undefining:Key %d, %s, %s\n",i,keys[i],
28727  (ig ? "Trapped." : "Freed."));
28728  if(ig){
28729  *keys[i]=0;
28730  lkeys[i]=0;
28731  }else{
28732  rmkey(keys,nkeys);
28733  }
28734  }else{ig=1;}
28735  }
28736 }

28738 void tth_enclose(str0,str1,str2,store) /* Enclose str1 with str0, str2 */
28739 char *str0, *str2, *str1, *store;
28740 { /* Exit if string gets more than 3.5 of the 4*max */
28741  int lost;
28742  strcpy(store,str1);
28743  if((lost=strlen(str2)+strlen(store)- TTH_34DLEN) < 0){
28744  strcat(store,str2);
28745  }else{
28746  fprintf(stderr,"**** Error: Fatal. String overflow: Lengths %d,%d\n",
28747  (int)strlen(store),(int)strlen(str2));
28748  fprintf(stderr,"Line %d\n",tth_num_lines);
28749  TTH_FATAL(2);
28750  }
28751  strcpy(str1,str0);
28752  if((lost=strlen(str1)+strlen(store)- TTH_34DLEN) < 0){
28753  strcat(str1,store);
28754  }else{
28755  fprintf(stderr,"**** Error: Fatal. String overflow: Lengths %d,%d\n",
28756  (int)strlen(store),(int)strlen(str1));
28757  fprintf(stderr,"Line %d\n",tth_num_lines);
28758  TTH_FATAL(2);
28759  }
28760 }
28761 
28762 void tth_prefix(str0,str1,store) /* Prefix str1 by str0, in str1 */
28763 char *str0, *str1, *store;
28764 {
28765  int lost;
28766  strcpy(store,str1);
28767  strcpy(str1,str0);
28768  if((lost=strlen(str1)+strlen(store)- TTH_34DLEN) < 0){
28769  strcat(str1,store);
28770  }else{
28771  fprintf(stderr,
28772  "**** Error: Fatal. Prefix string overflow: String %d, Prefix %d\n"
28773  ,(int)strlen(store),(int)strlen(str1));
28774  fprintf(stderr,"Line %d. Check for excessive length equation.\n%s\n"
28775  ,tth_num_lines," If necessary use switch -y0.");
28776  TTH_FATAL(2);
28777  }
28778 }
28779 /************************************************************************/
28780 /* start delimit */
28781 static void delimit(char *type, int heightin, char *codes)
28782  /* Return codes corresponding to a delimiter of given type and height*/
28783 {
28784 #define notypes 14
28785  static int top[notypes]={230,246,233,249,236,252,234,243,233,249,234,250,32,32};
28786  static int flat[notypes]={231,247,234,250,239,239,234,244,234,250,234,250,32,32};
28787  static int mid[notypes]={231,247,234,250,237,253,234,244,234,250,234,250,225,241};
28788  static int bot[notypes]={232,248,235,251,238,254,234,245,234,250,235,251,32,32};
28789  int i,j;
28790  char chr1[2]={0};
28791  char buff[20];
28792  int height;
28793  int horizmode=1; /* In equations use font tags not divs */
28794 
28795  /*tth_istyle case*/
28796  if(tth_istyle&1) height=0.65*heightin + 0.71; /* 2 has to yield 2*/
28797  else height=0.95*heightin+heightin*heightin/16 +.11;
28798  /* Experimental size. Evenness fixed. If very large assume matrix. */
28799  if(tth_debug&32)fprintf(stderr,"Delimiter %s, heightin=%d, height=%d\n",
28800  type,heightin,height);
28801 
28802  if (!strcmp(type,"(")) i=0 ;
28803  else if(!strcmp(type,")")) i=1 ;
28804  else if(!strcmp(type,"[")) i=2 ;
28805  else if(!strcmp(type,"]")) i=3 ;
28806  else if(!strcmp(type,"{")) {i=4 ; height=2*(height/2)+1;}
28807  else if(!strcmp(type,"}")) {i=5 ; height=2*(height/2)+1;}
28808  else if(!strcmp(type,"|")) i=6 ;
28809  else if(!strcmp(type,"&#242;")) i=7 ; /* int */
28810  else if(!strcmp(type,"&#233;")) i=8 ; /* lceil */
28811  else if(!strcmp(type,"&#249;")) i=9 ; /* rceil */
28812  else if(!strcmp(type,"&#235;")) i=10 ; /* lfloor */
28813  else if(!strcmp(type,"&#251;")) i=11 ; /* rfloor */
28814  else if(!strcmp(type,"&#225;")) i=12 ; /* langle */
28815  else if(!strcmp(type,"&#241;")) i=13 ; /* rangle */
28816  else if(!strcmp(type,"/") || !strcmp(type,"\\")) {
28817  /* Old version with font size=+... and bug sprintf(codes,
28818  "</td><td align=left>%s%d%s%s%s</td><td align=center>\n",
28819  TTH_SIZEGEN1,2*(height-1),TTH_SIZEGEN2,TTH_SIZEEND,type);
28820  */
28821  sprintf(codes,
28822  "</td><td align=left>%s%d%s%s%s</td><td align=center>\n",
28823  TTH_SIZEGEN1,100*(height),TTH_SIZEGEN2,type,TTH_SIZEEND);
28824  return;
28825  }
28826  else if(!strcmp(type,"&#214;")) { /* Sqrt code */
28827  if(tth_root_len[tth_root_depth]){ /* An index exists */
28828  if(heightin<=2 ){
28829  if(tth_istyle&1){
28830  sprintf(codes,"%s%s%s%s %s%s%s%s",TTH_CELL_R,TTH_OA1,
28831  TTH_FOOTNOTESIZE,tth_root_index[tth_root_depth],
28832  TTH_SIZEEND,TTH_OA2,TTH_SYMBOL,TTH_large);
28833  chr1[0]=214;
28834  sprintf(codes+strlen(codes),
28835  "%s%s%s%s%s",TTH_SYMPT(chr1),TTH_SIZEEND,TTH_SYMEND,TTH_OA3,TTH_CELL3);
28836  }else{
28837  chr1[0]=230;
28838  sprintf(codes,"%s\n%s%s %s%s%s%s<br />",
28839  TTH_CELL_R,TTH_SCRIPTSIZE,tth_root_index[tth_root_depth],
28840  TTH_SIZEEND,TTH_SYMBOL,TTH_NORMALSIZE,TTH_SYMPT(chr1));
28841  chr1[0]=214;
28842  sprintf(codes+strlen(codes),"%s <br />%s%s%s",
28843  TTH_SYMPT(chr1),TTH_SIZEEND,TTH_SYMEND,TTH_CELL3);
28844  }
28845  }else{
28846  chr1[0]=230;
28847  sprintf(codes,"%s%s%s%s %s%s%s%s<br />",TTH_CELL_R,TTH_OA5,TTH_SMALL,
28848  tth_root_index[tth_root_depth],TTH_SIZEEND,
28849  TTH_SYMBOL,TTH_Large,TTH_SYMPT(chr1));
28850  chr1[0]=231;
28851  for(j=1;j<(height*.78-2.3);j++){ /* extra sqrt height */
28852  sprintf(codes+strlen(codes),"%s<br />",TTH_SYMPT(chr1));
28853  }
28854  chr1[0]=214;
28855  if(tth_istyle&1) sprintf(codes+strlen(codes),
28856  "%s%s\n&nbsp;%s%s%s",TTH_SYMPT(chr1),TTH_SIZEEND,TTH_SYMEND,
28857  TTH_OA3,TTH_CELL3);
28858  else sprintf(codes+strlen(codes),"%s%s\n&nbsp;%s<br />\n%s",
28859  TTH_SYMPT(chr1),TTH_SIZEEND,TTH_SYMEND,
28860  TTH_CELL3);
28861  }
28862  }else{ /* Vanilla */
28863  if(heightin > 2){
28864  chr1[0]=230;
28865  sprintf(codes,
28866  "%s\n%s&nbsp;&nbsp;%s%s<br />"
28867  ,TTH_CELL_L,TTH_Large,TTH_SYMBOL,TTH_SYMPT(chr1));
28868  chr1[0]=250;
28869  for(j=1;j < (0.78*height-2.3);j++){
28870  sprintf(codes+strlen(codes),"%s&nbsp;%s%s<br />\n",
28871  TTH_SYMEND,TTH_SYMBOL,TTH_SYMPT(chr1));
28872  }/* Accommodate Konqueror nbsp symbol bug */
28873  chr1[0]=214;
28874  sprintf(codes+strlen(codes),"%s<br />%s%s%s",
28875  TTH_SYMPT(chr1),TTH_SIZEEND,TTH_SYMEND,TTH_CELL3);
28876  }else{
28877  chr1[0]=214;
28878  sprintf(codes,
28879  "%s<br />%s%s%s%s<br />%s%s%s",TTH_CELL_L,TTH_SYMBOL,
28880  TTH_Large,TTH_SYMPT(chr1),TTH_SIZEEND,TTH_SYMEND,TTH_OA4,TTH_CELL3);
28881  }
28882  }
28883  *tth_root_index[tth_root_depth]=0;
28884  tth_root_len[tth_root_depth]=0;
28885  tth_root_depth--;
28886  return;
28887  }
28888  else if(!strcmp(type,".")) { *codes=0; return; }
28889  else {
28890  fprintf(stderr, "Incorrect delimiter::%s::\n",type);
28891  i=-1;
28892  *codes=0;
28893  return;
28894  }
28895 
28896  /* Now using 8 bit codes. */
28897  if(height>1){
28898  strcpy(codes,TTH_CELL_L);
28899  strcat(codes,TTH_SYMBOLN);
28900  for (j=1 ; j <= height ; j++){
28901  if(j == 1) {chr1[0]=top[i]; sprintf(buff,"%s<br />",TTH_SYMPT(chr1));}
28902  else if(j == height) {chr1[0]=bot[i]; sprintf(buff,"%s\n",TTH_SYMPT(chr1));}
28903  else if(j == (height+1)/2) {
28904  chr1[0]=mid[i];sprintf(buff,"%s<br />\n",TTH_SYMPT(chr1));}
28905  else {chr1[0]=flat[i]; sprintf(buff,"%s<br />",TTH_SYMPT(chr1));}
28906  strcat(codes,buff);
28907  }
28908  strcat(codes,TTH_SYMEND);
28909  strcat(codes,TTH_CELL3);
28910  if(tth_debug&512) fprintf(stderr,"codes=%s",codes);
28911  }else{
28912  if(i > 6){
28913  strcpy(codes,TTH_SYMBOLN);
28914  strcat(codes,TTH_SYMPT(type));
28915  strcat(codes,TTH_SYMEND);
28916  }else strcpy(codes,type);
28917  }
28918 }
28919  /* end delimit */
28920  /*start symext*/
28921 /**************** Construct large, possibly extended, character. */
28922 void tth_symext(charin,charout)
28923 char *charin,*charout;
28924 {
28925  int horizmode=1; /* In equations use font tags not divs */
28926  char chr1[2]={0};
28927  chr1[0]=242;
28928  if(strlen(charin) == 1){
28929  if(charin[0]==chr1[0]) {
28930  strcpy(charout,TTH_SYMBOL);
28931  chr1[0]=243;strcat(charout,TTH_SYMPT(chr1));
28932  strcat(charout,"<br />");
28933  chr1[0]=245;strcat(charout,TTH_SYMPT(chr1));
28934  strcat(charout,"<br />");
28935  strcat(charout,TTH_SYMEND);
28936  }else {
28937  strcpy(charout,TTH_LARGE);
28938  strcat(charout,TTH_SYMBOL);
28939  strcat(charout,TTH_SYMPT(charin));
28940  strcat(charout,"<br />\n") ;
28941  strcat(charout,TTH_SYMEND);
28942  strcat(charout,TTH_SIZEEND);
28943  }
28944  }else{ /* Longer than one: remove a leading space, quote and terminate. */
28945  if(*charin==' ')strcpy(charout,charin+1); else strcpy(charout,charin);
28946  if(strstr(charout,TTH_OBR)+strlen(TTH_OBR)!=charout+strlen(charout)
28947  && strstr(charout, /*This mess is really TTH_DIV without eqclose ref*/
28948  (tth_istyle&1 ?
28949  "\n<div class=\"hrcomp\"><hr noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"1\"/></div>"
28950  :"<hr noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"1\" />")
28951  )+strlen(
28952  (tth_istyle&1 ?
28953  "\n<div class=\"hrcomp\"><hr noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"1\"/></div>"
28954  :"<hr noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"1\" />")
28955  )!=charout+strlen(charout)
28956  && strstr(charout+strlen(charout)-9,"ble>")==NULL)
28957  strcat(charout,"<br />\n");
28958  } /* Don't add an extra br to a hr or table end. */
28959 }
28960  /*end symext*/
28961 /***************** Encode 3-digit integers *************************/
28962 void tth_encode(code,num)
28963 char *code;
28964 int num;
28965 {
28966 int i;
28967 sprintf(code,"%03d",num);
28968 for (i=0;i<3;i++) *(code+i)=*(code+i) + 17;
28969 }

28971 /*******************************************************************/
28972 /* Find the first brace group in the string "text" and copy it to the
28973  string group, whose maximum length is len, value returned 0 if successful.*/
28974 int tth_group(group,text,len)
28975 char *text,*group;
28976 int len;
28977 {
28978  int i,j;
28979  int brace;
28980  i=strspn(text," \t\n");
28981  /* if(*(text+i)=='{') i++; remove leading brace */
28982  j=0;
28983  brace=0; /* 1 if removing braces */
28984  while(i+j < strlen(text)){
28985  if(*(text+i+j)=='{')brace++;
28986  else if(*(text+i+j)=='}')brace--;
28987  if(brace <= 0) break;
28988  j++;
28989  }
28990  strncpy(group,text+i,len);
28991  if(i+j<len) *(group+i+j+1)=0;
28992  return brace;
28993 }
28994 
28995 /*******************************************************************/
28996 /* Convert an integer into roman numerals. */
28997 static int roman(int num, char *rm)
28998 {
28999 #define CODENUM 8
29000  int i,j,k,m,n,p;
29001  int multiples[CODENUM]={1000,500,100,50,10,5,1,0};
29002  char codes[CODENUM]={'m','d','c','l','x','v','i',' '};
29003  if(abs(num) >= 4*multiples[0]){
29004  strcpy(rm,"A LARGE NUMBER");
29005  return 1;
29006  }
29007  m=0;
29008  i=num;
29009  if(i < 0){
29010  i=-i;
29011  *(rm+(m++))='-';
29012  }
29013  for(j=0;j<CODENUM-1;j++){
29014  k=multiples[j];
29015  while(i-k>=0){
29016  i=i-k;
29017  *(rm+(m++))=codes[j];
29018  }
29019  if(j<CODENUM-2){
29020  n=(j/2)*2+2;
29021  p=multiples[n];
29022  if(i+p>=k){
29023  i=i-(k-p);
29024  *(rm+(m++))=codes[n];
29025  *(rm+(m++))=codes[j];
29026  }
29027  }
29028  }
29029  *(rm+(m++))=0;
29030  return 0;
29031 }
29032 /* start b_align */
29033 /*************************************************************************
29034  Take off the Cell start and the extra bottom from single over construct.
29035  This is used only at the completion of the top or bottom of a fraction.
29036  If cell starts or ends with CELL3, cut off since they are redundant.
29037  If it then ends with OA4 it is a candidate for bottom removal.
29038  If every CELL3 appears as part of the sequence OA4 CELL3, then change
29039  each occurrence to just CELL3.
29040  */
29041 #define BMAXLEN 1000
29042 #define NSTS 20
29043 static int b_align(thestring,tth_debug)
29044  char *thestring;
29045  int tth_debug;
29046 {
29047  char buff1[BMAXLEN];
29048  char *chr,*chr1,*chr2;
29049  char *oastarts[NSTS];
29050  char *oa4null=" ";
29051  int ists=0,i;
29052 
29053  if(tth_debug&8192)fprintf(stderr,"b_align string:%s",thestring);
29054  if(strlen(thestring) > BMAXLEN) return 0; /*Too long*/
29055  strcpy(buff1,thestring);
29056  if(strstr(thestring,TTH_CELL3) == thestring) { /*Starts with CELL3 */
29057  strcpy(buff1,thestring+strlen(TTH_CELL3));
29058  if(tth_debug&2)fprintf(stderr,"String Head cut, ");
29059  }
29060  if(strstr(buff1+strlen(buff1)-strlen(TTH_CELL3),TTH_CELL3)){/*end*/
29061  *(buff1+strlen(buff1)-strlen(TTH_CELL3))=0;
29062  if(tth_debug&2)fprintf(stderr,"String Tail cut. ");
29063  }
29064  if((oastarts[0]=strstr(buff1+strlen(buff1)-strlen(TTH_OA4),TTH_OA4))){
29065  chr=buff1;
29066  for (ists=0; ists<NSTS; ists++) {
29067  if((chr1=strstr(chr,TTH_CELL3))){
29068  chr2=chr1-strlen(TTH_OA4);
29069  if(chr2-chr<0){ists=-1; break;}
29070  if(strstr(chr2,TTH_OA4)!=chr2){ists=-2; break;}
29071  oastarts[ists+1]=chr2;
29072  chr=chr1+strlen(TTH_CELL3);
29073  }else{
29074  break;
29075  }
29076  } /* We exit with ists=number of OA-CELLs or - if non-treatable. */
29077  for (i=0;i<=ists;i++) {
29078  strncpy(oastarts[i],oa4null,strlen(TTH_OA4));
29079  }
29080  if(tth_debug&2)fprintf(stderr,"String OA4 removed %d times:\n%s\n",
29081  ists+1,buff1);
29082  }
29083  strcpy(thestring,buff1);
29084  return (ists+1);
29085 } /* end b_align */
29086 /****************************************************************************
29087 Convert a dimension into scaled points. 1pt = 2^16 = 65536 sp.
29088 1pc =12pt = 786432 sp
29089 1in =72.27pt =4736287 sp
29090 1bp =72.27/72pt =1.0038 pt= 65785 sp
29091 1cm =1in/2.54 = 1864680 sp
29092 1mm = 18648 sp
29093 1dd =1238/1157 pt = 70124 sp
29094 1cc = 12 dd = 841489 sp
29095 1em = width of a quad (capital M, actually the height of it)
29096 1ex = height of 'x'.
29097 
29098 This needs 4 byte integers.
29099 */
29100 #define EMPOINTS 12
29101 #define ENPOINTS 6
29102 #define EXPOINTS 10
29103 static int scaledpoints(thenumber,thedimension)
29104  float thenumber;
29105  char *thedimension;
29106 {
29107 int dimval;
29108 if(strstr(thedimension,"pt")==thedimension)dimval=65536;
29109 else if(strstr(thedimension,"pc")==thedimension)dimval=786432;
29110 else if(strstr(thedimension,"in")==thedimension)dimval=4736287;
29111 else if(strstr(thedimension,"bp")==thedimension)dimval=65785;
29112 else if(strstr(thedimension,"cm")==thedimension)dimval=1864680;
29113 else if(strstr(thedimension,"mm")==thedimension)dimval=186468;
29114 else if(strstr(thedimension,"dd")==thedimension)dimval=70124;
29115 else if(strstr(thedimension,"cc")==thedimension)dimval=841489;
29116 else if(strstr(thedimension,"ex")==thedimension)dimval=EXPOINTS*65536;
29117 else if(strstr(thedimension,"em")==thedimension)dimval=EMPOINTS*65536;
29118 else if(strstr(thedimension,"en")==thedimension)dimval=ENPOINTS*65536;
29119 else if(strstr(thedimension,"sp")==thedimension)dimval=1;
29120 else dimval=1;
29121 return ((int) (dimval*thenumber));
29122 }
29123 
29124 /* Add dimension 2 into dimension 1*/
29125 static int adddimen(number1,unit1,number2,unit2)
29126  float *number1,*number2;
29127  char *unit1,*unit2;
29128 {
29129  if(*unit1=='%'){/* hsize supercedes others */
29130  if(*unit2=='%') {
29131  *number1=*number1+*number2;
29132  }else{
29133  *number1=*number1+
29134  (((double)scaledpoints(*number2,unit2))/SCALEDPERPIXEL)/DEFAULTHSIZEPIX;
29135  strcpy(unit1,"%");
29136  }
29137  }else{
29138  if(*unit2=='%'){
29139  *number1=*number2+
29140  (((double)scaledpoints(*number1,unit1))/SCALEDPERPIXEL)/DEFAULTHSIZEPIX;
29141  strcpy(unit1,"%");
29142  }else{ /* Both absolute. Return absolute scaled points.*/
29143  *number1=scaledpoints(*number1,unit1)+scaledpoints(*number2,unit2);
29144  strcpy(unit1,"sp");
29145  return 1; /* Absolute units */
29146  }
29147  }
29148  return 0; /* Percentage */
29149 }

29261 /*************************************
29262 Convert a symbol character 8859 reference into unicode point
29263 If the input string chsym is of length 1, just use its 8 bit code.
29264 If not, try to read the first positive integer from it.
29265 If that fails, translate every character separately.
29266 The returned value is a pointer to the global string chuni
29267 containing the unicode HTML numeric ref(s) on return.
29268 */
29269 
29270 char tth_chuni[TTH_CHARLEN];
29271 
29272 char* tth_symbol_point(chsym)
29273  char *chsym;
29274 {
29275  /* this table is based on the test/symbols.html file of MathML*/
29276  /* It is used if the global tth_unicode == 1 */
29277 char *tth_sympoint[256]={
29278 /*0*/ "&nbsp;",/*1*/ "&nbsp;",/*2*/ "&nbsp;",/*3*/ "&nbsp;",
29279 /*4*/ "&nbsp;",/*5*/ "&nbsp;",/*6*/ "&nbsp;",/*7*/ "&nbsp;",
29280 /*8*/ "&nbsp;",/*9*/ "&nbsp;",/*10*/ "&nbsp;",/*11*/ "&nbsp;",
29281 /*12*/ "&nbsp;",/*13*/ "&nbsp;",/*14*/ "&nbsp;",/*15*/ "&nbsp;",
29282 /*16*/ "&nbsp;",/*17*/ "&nbsp;",/*18*/ "&nbsp;",/*19*/ "&nbsp;",
29283 /*20*/ "&nbsp;",/*21*/ "&nbsp;",/*22*/ "&nbsp;",/*23*/ "&nbsp;",
29284 /*24*/ "&nbsp;",/*25*/ "&nbsp;",/*26*/ "&nbsp;",/*27*/ "&nbsp;",
29285 /*28*/ "&nbsp;",/*29*/ "&nbsp;",/*30*/ "&nbsp;",/*31*/ "&nbsp;",
29286 /*32*/ "&#160;",/*33*/ "&#33;",/*34*/ "&#8704;",/*35*/ "&#35;",
29287 /*36*/ "&#8707;",/*37*/ "&#37;",/*38*/ "&#38;",/*39*/ "&#8715;",
29288 /*40*/ "&#40;",/*41*/ "&#41;",/*42*/ "&#8727;",/*43*/ "&#43;",
29289 /*44*/ "&#44;",/*45*/ "&#8722;",/*46*/ "&#46;",/*47*/ "&#47;",
